CAPE TOWN - A 15-year-old boy died in hospital after he was shot dead following clashes between rival gangs in Bramble Road, Bonteheuwel at the weekend.The provincial health department said, Emergency Medical Services (EMS) responded to the incident and transported him to hospital where he succumbed to his injuries.“Western Cape Government Health’s EMS responded to an incident which involved a 15-year-old male who sustained a fatal gunshot head wound after being shot in Bramble Street, Bonteheuwel on Saturday, February 12 at 19:21. An ambulance was dispatched and transported the patient to Groote Schuur Hospital. Unfortunately, the patient passed away at Groote Schuur Hospital. The body of the dead was transported to Salt River Mortuary,” provincial health spokesperson, Deanna February said.She added that the health department extended their condolences to the family of the dead.Police said they believed the shooting was gang-related but no arrests had been made at this stage.“Last night at about 19:30 a 15-year-old male person was shot and killed in Bramble Road Bonteheuwel by an unknown suspect who is yet to be arrested. We have reason to believe the incident is motivated by gang activity in the area. The circumstances of the murder are being investigated,” police spokesperson Andre Traut said.Read more in Monday’s edition of the Cape Times. Cape Times